-- Microsoft ups FY08 business unit growth forecasts
-- 
-- Thu Oct 25, 2007 5:21pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/10/25/us-microsoft-results-outlook-idUSWNAS848920071025

 

 LOS ANGELES  (Reuters) - Microsoft Corp ( MSFT.O ), the world's largest software maker, on Thursday raised full-year revenue forecasts across all of its business units. 

 The company said it now sees revenue from its Windows client division growing 12 percent to 13 percent, compared with 9 percent to 10 percent previously. It said full-year server and tools division revenue growth was now forecast at 16 percent to 18 percent, up from 14 percent to 15 percent. Office business division revenue is seen growing 14 percent to 15 percent, compared with 11 percent to 12 percent. Revenue from its online services unit is now expected to grow 33 percent to 37 percent versus Microsoft's prior call for growth of 10 percent to 13 percent. Fiscal 2008 entertainment and devices division revenue, which includes sales of its Xbox 360 video game console, is now seen growing 15 percent to 20 percent versus 10 percent to 19 percent previously. (Reporting by  Lisa Baertlein )